description: In Dame Darcy's neo-Victorian world of two-headed beauties, mermaids and deathly adventures, the horrible and shadowy people are the most seductive. Most recently seen in Alan Moore's Tomorrow Stories, Dame Darcy continues to delight us with her wicked sense of play with more Meat Cake! This issue: Hindrance and Perfida reclaim their ruby choker stolen by a criminal lady and find Richard's husband in the process, Tommaso Nicolao lends his dark pen to lithely illustrate a tragic ghost story, and fine, delicious recipes from the Latchkey Kids Cookbook. Plus the beautiful continuation of the watery "Planet Blue" story.

description:
Sir Arthur Conan Doyle's most well known creation is undoubtedly, Sherlock Holmes. But yet another character he created also has a rightful place in the great fictional characters of all time, Professor Challenger. A fore runner to adventures such as Doc Savage, Professor Challenger was a scientist who used his strength and masterful wit to explore such wonders as The Lost World and the Disintegration Machine.

In this first adaptation, The Poison Belt, by Donald Marquez (The Realm), the world is plunged into an abyss of poisonous gas that is slowly choking the life from the land. The Professor must persevere to save not only his life, but of the planet as well!
